{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, most existing methods fail to effectively extract crucial clues from user comments on social networks.",
    "To tackle these challenges, Liu et al. (2022) introduced a social network rumor detection method, called DAGCN (dual attention graph convolutional network).",
    "DAGCN combines a dual attention mechanism with a graph convolutional network to enhance the detection of rumors in social networks.",
    "It constructs a heterogeneous propagation graph for each event by utilizing the comment-retweet relationship.",
    "In this graph, different events are represented as nodes, while the edges represent the connections between users."
  ]
}